  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Clean Water &amp; Sanitation for Schools in Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DACT brings their first water ever to people in remote places in Africa. This project will provide a water well to people in need in rural Nigeria. Supporting education and improved health for 2,500 people across communities and schools, this project will provide training to pump caretakers and WASH Committees on preventive maintenance of dysfunctional water wells. The project will expand access to safe drinking water, improved conditions of health and increased school attendance for Children.</narrative>
  </description>
